37:51.837 --> 37:53.339
Are you serious?

37:54.673 --> 37:55.941
Yeah.

37:56.942 --> 38:01.780
It's just... You were right.
We're not my parents.

38:01.880 --> 38:06.918
Whatever their problems were,
that's their story.

38:07.018 --> 38:10.021
But we should have
a chance at our own.

38:11.890 --> 38:15.694
So, I don't know,
I think...

38:18.564 --> 38:20.165
I think we should do this.

38:26.805 --> 38:28.139
Are you sure?

38:29.675 --> 38:31.410
'Cause I just don't
want to do it if
you're not totally...

38:31.510 --> 38:32.678
Yes, I'm sure.

38:34.646 --> 38:36.382
But there's one condition.

38:36.448 --> 38:37.683
Okay. Yeah.

38:40.586 --> 38:42.521
I want you to ask me again.

38:45.524 --> 38:48.394
But I want us to pretend
like it's the first time.

38:51.630 --> 38:54.733
Yeah. Yeah, of course. Okay.

38:57.403 --> 38:58.404
Um...

39:00.038 --> 39:01.573
Uh, yeah.

39:01.673 --> 39:04.042
No. Not here.

39:05.310 --> 39:06.612
What do you mean?

39:23.895 --> 39:25.431
- It's so beautiful.

39:27.566 --> 39:28.567
- Yep.

39:29.300 --> 39:30.736
Here we are again.

39:35.140 --> 39:36.975
Glad I didn't toss this.

39:43.081 --> 39:44.450
You ready?

39:47.919 --> 39:49.621
We're really doing this, huh?

40:03.134 --> 40:07.405
Ruth Miller,
will you spend the rest
of your life with me?

40:11.242 --> 40:12.678
Yes, I will.

40:26.458 --> 40:28.326
Damn, that looks good on you.

40:37.068 --> 40:39.471
That is the most
incredible thing
I have ever felt.

40:47.178 --> 40:48.814
I love you, Harry.

40:52.183 --> 40:53.218
- I love you.

40:55.487 --> 40:57.155
- No. No, no! No.

43:15.026 --> 43:16.227
- Oh, my God.

43:18.229 --> 43:19.665
Oh, my God.

43:24.069 --> 43:25.136
Oh.

43:26.872 --> 43:28.106
Viv?

43:28.840 --> 43:29.941
Vivian!

43:33.879 --> 43:35.146
Oh, my God.

43:39.250 --> 43:40.686
Are you okay?

43:41.687 --> 43:43.689
She's dehydrated.

43:47.258 --> 43:50.261
It's okay.
Just take a sip.

43:52.163 --> 43:53.164
Mm?

44:02.473 --> 44:06.277
Now, what happened to you?

44:09.380 --> 44:10.882
I don't remember.

44:13.551 --> 44:14.886
I'll call 911.

44:20.225 --> 44:22.227
Shit. No service.

44:25.163 --> 44:28.633
- You know what?
We're about to set up camp.

44:28.734 --> 44:31.136
Why don't you
come with us, huh?

44:32.203 --> 44:34.439
We'll get
some food in you.
Would you like that?

44:38.977 --> 44:40.078
Ray?

44:41.212 --> 44:42.313
Yeah.

44:57.763 --> 44:58.864
Still nothing.

44:58.964 --> 45:01.066
I know. Quiet as a mouse.

45:02.200 --> 45:04.269
I'm gonna give it
another shot.

45:10.508 --> 45:12.077
Hey there, hon.

45:17.816 --> 45:19.417
You feeling better?

45:23.789 --> 45:26.491
We're gonna head back
first thing in the morning,
I promise.

45:26.591 --> 45:32.430
But you, um, ready to tell us
what happened to you?

45:34.599 --> 45:36.334
I said I don't remember.

45:39.137 --> 45:42.507
Maybe you have
a campsite close by?

45:45.977 --> 45:47.278
What about your gear?

45:47.378 --> 45:51.382
You didn't have anything
with you. I mean,
were you alone?

45:54.652 --> 45:57.956
You didn't come
all the way out here
by yourself, did you?

46:04.062 --> 46:07.833
You know what?
Forget about it then.

46:07.866 --> 46:09.667
You'll remember
when you remember.

46:11.369 --> 46:13.704
Let's talk about
something else, huh?

46:14.405 --> 46:15.573
Um...

46:15.673 --> 46:20.245
What do you like
to do, Ruth?
You got any hobbies?

46:22.680 --> 46:24.049
I...

46:27.919 --> 46:29.855
...like to surf.

46:29.888 --> 46:32.457
Oh! That's great. Us, too.

46:33.391 --> 46:36.761
You know, we used to
lug our shortboards

46:36.862 --> 46:37.863
out to the beach here,

46:37.929 --> 46:40.065
but the last few times
we did,

46:40.165 --> 46:43.101
there were
way too many sharks.

46:43.201 --> 46:46.972
Global warming
pushes them all
inland. So...

46:55.780 --> 46:58.716
Honey, are you all right?

47:09.194 --> 47:13.664
You know, I'm gonna go
walk out a little further,

47:13.764 --> 47:18.603
and see if I can find
some service.
Get a call out.

47:29.180 --> 47:31.917
I think something's
really wrong with her.

47:32.017 --> 47:34.419
Honey, I don't think
we can wait until morning.

47:34.519 --> 47:35.553
Okay.

47:38.756 --> 47:40.158
Sweetheart...

47:43.361 --> 47:45.263
What are you doing
with that?

48:06.384 --> 48:08.486
Come on, kid.
Put that thing down.

48:11.022 --> 48:12.257
No.

48:13.291 --> 48:15.326
- Hey. There you are.

48:16.461 --> 48:17.795
- Who is that guy?

48:19.130 --> 48:20.165
Oh!

48:20.265 --> 48:21.466
It's him.

48:24.669 --> 48:25.703
Hey, Ruth.

48:26.571 --> 48:27.638
What the fuck?

48:28.139 --> 48:29.975
No. No.

48:30.675 --> 48:31.977
No.

48:32.010 --> 48:33.844
- Hey.
That's close enough.

48:35.113 --> 48:36.347
Who are your friends?

48:36.447 --> 48:37.582
No, no.
We're right here, honey.

48:37.682 --> 48:38.984
No, we have to run.
No, it's okay.

48:39.050 --> 48:40.485
Where are you going?

48:41.586 --> 48:43.054
Come back!

48:43.154 --> 48:46.591
Last time I'm gonna
tell you, buddy. Just stay
the fuck where you are!

48:46.691 --> 48:48.326
Whoa, whoa, whoa. You're being
a little aggressive, dude.

48:48.426 --> 48:49.494
All right.
You had your warning.

48:49.594 --> 48:51.862
Hey. Relax, man.
I come in peace.

49:10.648 --> 49:13.551
Hey. Thanks for finding her.

49:16.887 --> 49:17.888
Ruth?

49:19.757 --> 49:20.758
Oh, God.

49:25.296 --> 49:27.365
What are you doing?

49:27.465 --> 49:28.899
We have to hide.
Okay.

49:34.039 --> 49:35.106
Who is that guy?

49:35.206 --> 49:36.841
Is he your boyfriend?

49:39.110 --> 49:41.879
That is not Harry.

49:47.352 --> 49:50.455
- Hello! Viv!

49:50.555 --> 49:52.457
No, no, no. Please.
Please, no. Stay.

49:52.557 --> 49:55.626
Sweetheart, it's okay.
It's just Ray.
It's my husband.

49:56.894 --> 49:58.263
Over here.

50:02.833 --> 50:04.035
- Thank God.

50:05.236 --> 50:06.671
Are you okay?

50:06.771 --> 50:07.905
I'm okay.

50:09.374 --> 50:10.608
- Well...

50:12.510 --> 50:14.379
Well, what about that guy?

50:16.114 --> 50:17.082
Well, where's he?

50:23.154 --> 50:25.156
Right behind me.

50:45.943 --> 50:47.078
Come on out, Ruth.

50:51.249 --> 50:52.883
I'm gonna kill her
if you don't.

51:05.596 --> 51:08.166
Hey. There's our girl.

51:11.802 --> 51:13.204
What did you do to her?

51:14.339 --> 51:16.006
Her?

51:16.141 --> 51:21.146
Oh, don't worry.
I can fix that. Watch.

51:27.152 --> 51:28.919
No!

51:31.722 --> 51:32.957
How did you know?

51:36.527 --> 51:38.663
How?
I don't wanna die.

51:38.763 --> 51:41.031
I saw where you took him.

51:44.169 --> 51:45.836
I found the cave.

51:54.011 --> 51:55.180
What the hell?

52:09.294 --> 52:10.695
Oh, my God.

52:12.330 --> 52:13.498
Harry.

52:34.819 --> 52:37.322
Oh, God. Oh, God.

53:00.278 --> 53:01.346
- Ruth!

53:02.513 --> 53:03.814
Ruth!

53:04.515 --> 53:05.950
Ruth! Jesus Christ.

53:07.252 --> 53:08.319
Hey!

53:09.587 --> 53:10.821
- I saw him.

53:11.556 --> 53:13.891
Fuck. The cave.

53:14.925 --> 53:16.494
I knew it was too close.

53:22.667 --> 53:24.935
What are you?

53:25.035 --> 53:27.538
I'm pissed off
is what I am, Ruth.

53:33.578 --> 53:35.313
I'm a scout.

53:35.413 --> 53:37.748
I get to the planet first,
then I report back
to the others.

53:37.848 --> 53:39.650
What am I fucking doing?

53:39.750 --> 53:41.118
What am I doing
telling you this?

53:44.489 --> 53:45.490
Goodbye, Ruth.

53:45.590 --> 53:47.992
No, no, no. No. Please.

53:48.092 --> 53:49.093
Please.

53:50.328 --> 53:54.164
What am I doing?
Just do it. Just do it.

53:59.136 --> 54:00.204
Goodbye, Ruth.

54:00.305 --> 54:04.642
No, no. No. I don't...
Please. Please.

54:04.742 --> 54:06.311
What the fuck
is wrong with me?

54:06.377 --> 54:09.847
All the creatures
I could stumble upon,
I gotta be this guy.

54:09.947 --> 54:11.949
Okay.

54:12.049 --> 54:18.155
I was better off
as the deer. Just do it!
Just do it.

54:18.323 --> 54:20.858
No, please. I won't
tell anyone. I promise.

54:20.958 --> 54:23.761
I promise I won't tell.
I won't.

54:39.710 --> 54:41.946
No. Wait, what...

54:43.614 --> 54:44.949
Do I love you?

54:46.551 --> 54:48.419
Like, do I love you?
Is that...

54:51.021 --> 54:52.590
Is that even possible?

54:57.362 --> 54:58.463
How the...

55:04.869 --> 55:06.371
I love your hands.

55:08.373 --> 55:09.374
What the...

55:11.075 --> 55:12.443
I love your smile.

55:13.978 --> 55:15.380
I love your laugh.

55:17.515 --> 55:18.683
Fuck!

55:20.551 --> 55:21.652
I love you.

55:23.187 --> 55:24.755
I love you, Ruth.

55:25.390 --> 55:26.090
No! Wait!

55:33.063 --> 55:35.700
Ruth! You don't
have to worry.

55:37.134 --> 55:38.569
I'm not gonna hurt you.

55:40.004 --> 55:41.271
I love you!

55:43.874 --> 55:45.676
Oh, it feels incredible!

55:54.419 --> 55:56.421
Ruth, let me explain.

55:56.521 --> 55:58.556
Okay.

55:59.189 --> 56:00.625
I see that you're angry.

56:02.893 --> 56:04.228
Get away from me.

56:04.328 --> 56:05.496
Hey. Why don't we
just calm down
and talk about this?

56:09.834 --> 56:10.968
This is so us.

56:11.068 --> 56:13.771
Look, I understand why
you're angry. I killed Harry.

56:13.871 --> 56:16.874
But, silver lining,
I am Harry.

56:16.974 --> 56:18.443
No, you're not.

56:18.476 --> 56:20.478
No. I literally am.
I'm an exact biological
replication of him.

56:20.578 --> 56:23.113
All of his thoughts,
his fears, his memories
are my thoughts,

56:23.213 --> 56:24.482
my fears, my memories.

56:24.582 --> 56:26.183
Our first date was
at the Sherwood Fair.

56:26.283 --> 56:27.785
I kissed you
on the Thunder Bolt.
What? Stop. Stop!

56:27.885 --> 56:29.687
Hey, Ruth. Hear me out.

56:30.755 --> 56:31.922
I've been
so many different things.

56:32.022 --> 56:33.758
I thought I felt everything
there was to feel, right?

56:33.858 --> 56:36.594
It turns out, I realized now,
I wasn't actually feeling
those things.

56:36.694 --> 56:38.763
It was just whatever I was
that was feeling them.

56:38.863 --> 56:41.866
But for some reason,
as soon as I felt love,
all of a sudden

56:41.966 --> 56:43.934
I was feeling those feelings.

56:44.034 --> 56:46.904
And not just feeling
the feeling of something else
feeling those feelings.

56:47.004 --> 56:48.305
Do you know what I mean?

56:51.308 --> 56:53.711
What do you want from me?

56:56.113 --> 56:57.347
I...

57:05.055 --> 57:06.524
I wanna
show you something.

57:34.652 --> 57:35.686
You know,
the craziest thing is,

57:35.786 --> 57:38.556
love doesn't even exist
anywhere else.

57:38.656 --> 57:41.258
It's a singularly
human emotion.

57:41.358 --> 57:44.194
Like, of all
the different things
that I've been,

57:44.294 --> 57:46.597
none of 'em feel it.
Isn't that nuts?

57:49.534 --> 57:51.401
Just tell me
where we're going.

57:52.737 --> 57:54.905
What part of
"it's a surprise"
don't you get?

57:58.876 --> 57:59.944
All right, you know what?

58:01.278 --> 58:02.547
You've been patient.

58:03.347 --> 58:04.615
You ready?

58:05.950 --> 58:07.051
For what?

58:16.260 --> 58:17.928
It's a pretty
sweet ride, right?

58:20.297 --> 58:22.567
Oh, my God.

58:30.307 --> 58:31.576
All right.

58:32.577 --> 58:35.946
Look, I know you love Earth.

58:36.046 --> 58:40.184
I just think a change
of scenery could be
really good for you.

58:40.284 --> 58:42.286
You know, just mentally.

58:42.386 --> 58:43.788
Obviously, here you've got
a lot of triggers,

58:43.888 --> 58:46.857
a lot of stressors,
but if we go someplace else,

58:46.957 --> 58:48.192
some quiet little planet,

58:48.292 --> 58:52.129
somewhere no one
will ever find us,
we got a fresh start.

58:56.266 --> 58:57.635
Bigger thing is,

58:59.236 --> 59:00.705
I really care about you,

59:01.639 --> 59:03.874
and I just don't want
to see you get hurt.

59:05.610 --> 59:07.778
There are a lot more
like me coming.

59:08.813 --> 59:11.415
They are gonna blend in
and take over,

59:11.515 --> 59:15.052
and they are gonna turn
this planet into a place
that you don't wanna be.

59:16.286 --> 59:17.521
Trust me.

59:21.892 --> 59:23.794
I can give you
an incredible life, Ruth.

59:25.663 --> 59:27.031
I really can.

59:30.167 --> 59:31.636
What do you say?

59:36.340 --> 59:37.642
Okay.

59:40.077 --> 59:41.646
Yeah?

59:41.679 --> 59:43.648
Yeah, you're serious?
Yeah.

59:50.520 --> 59:52.556
All right. All right.

59:52.657 --> 59:54.124
That's what
I'm talking about.

59:54.224 --> 59:56.393
You're gonna flip
when you see the inside
of this thing.

59:56.493 --> 59:59.664
I mean, it looks tight,
but once you're inside,
it's like a mansion.

59:59.764 --> 1:00:01.131
It's kind of hard...

1:00:02.499 --> 1:00:05.202
Oh, come on. Are we
really gonna do this again?

1:00:05.302 --> 1:00:06.871
Just get in the ship, Ruth.

1:00:09.473 --> 1:00:10.708
Oh, God.

1:00:13.243 --> 1:00:14.712
You've gotta
be kidding me.

1:00:21.218 --> 1:00:22.252
Ruth!

1:00:23.888 --> 1:00:24.889
Ruth!

1:00:29.827 --> 1:00:30.828
Ruth!

1:00:44.909 --> 1:00:45.910
Ruth!

1:00:48.746 --> 1:00:50.314
You're gonna drown.

1:00:52.950 --> 1:00:55.686
Come on!
You're being ridiculous.

1:01:00.557 --> 1:01:02.860
Ruth, please!

1:01:02.960 --> 1:01:05.763
Ruth,
what is the endgame
here? Seriously.

1:01:07.097 --> 1:01:08.866
Oh, do not look
at me like that.

1:01:08.966 --> 1:01:12.136
I'm just trying to help.
Let's just head back
and talk...

1:03:40.384 --> 1:03:41.986
Oh, my God.

1:04:51.788 --> 1:04:53.323
Oh, no.

1:05:45.775 --> 1:05:47.544
I don't understand, Ruth.

1:05:49.013 --> 1:05:50.547
Why do you keep running?

1:05:54.251 --> 1:05:55.885
I'm trying to save you.

1:05:58.088 --> 1:05:59.789
Don't you wanna be saved?

1:07:09.559 --> 1:07:11.728
You know, it didn't
have to be this way.

1:07:13.630 --> 1:07:15.832
I just wanted us to love
each other, Ruth.

1:07:17.634 --> 1:07:19.203
I was never gonna
hurt you.

1:07:21.571 --> 1:07:24.808
It could have been
so easy.

1:07:34.318 --> 1:07:35.885
But you didn't want that.

1:07:37.387 --> 1:07:38.955
So I found another way.

1:07:45.129 --> 1:07:46.830
An even purer form of love.

1:07:52.502 --> 1:07:54.138
What do you think
love is, Ruth?

1:07:57.141 --> 1:07:58.242
It's desire.

1:07:59.309 --> 1:08:02.045
Sure, but for what?

1:08:02.146 --> 1:08:05.215
It can't be as simple as
wanting to spend time
with someone...

1:08:06.483 --> 1:08:08.185
Or have sex with them,

1:08:09.018 --> 1:08:11.155
or share
your darkest secrets...

1:08:13.657 --> 1:08:15.892
Because you and Harry
did all those things,

1:08:17.026 --> 1:08:19.663
and never once
did his love weaken.

1:08:25.202 --> 1:08:26.603
But shouldn't it?

1:08:28.238 --> 1:08:30.407
Hunger passes when we eat.

1:08:30.507 --> 1:08:33.277
Exhaustion fades
when we sleep.

1:08:34.478 --> 1:08:36.246
But that's not true
for love.

1:08:38.014 --> 1:08:40.784
That's what
makes it so unique.

1:08:41.785 --> 1:08:43.687
The goal is unattainable.

1:08:45.389 --> 1:08:50.294
It's two souls
desperately wanting
to become one.

1:08:51.895 --> 1:08:56.266
And that is a desire
human beings
could never fulfill.

1:09:11.581 --> 1:09:12.916
But I can.

1:09:36.005 --> 1:09:39.276
I've been longing
to see inside of you.

1:09:40.910 --> 1:09:45.415
All the colors,
the electricity, the passion.

1:09:48.685 --> 1:09:50.053
The love.

1:09:53.623 --> 1:09:54.991
You do love him.

1:10:01.431 --> 1:10:03.267
But so much pain.

1:10:08.372 --> 1:10:10.374
It makes so much sense now.

1:10:13.843 --> 1:10:16.246
I feel like I finally
understand you.

1:10:21.551 --> 1:10:23.052
Don't worry.

1:10:25.822 --> 1:10:28.458
I won't let your pain
hold you back any longer.

1:10:31.227 --> 1:10:33.963
I'm gonna live the life
you always should have.

1:10:36.733 --> 1:10:38.968
I'm gonna make something
out of you.

1:10:41.771 --> 1:10:43.139
Goodbye, Ruth.

1:10:44.341 --> 1:10:48.177
No. That's not possible.

1:10:50.246 --> 1:10:52.048
What's that?

1:10:52.148 --> 1:10:55.118
You said you won't let my pain
hold you back.

1:10:57.186 --> 1:11:02.526
But that's not possible
because you can't control it.

1:11:03.993 --> 1:11:06.663
The pain is a part of you.

1:11:06.763 --> 1:11:11.134
You can't separate it
from who you are.

1:11:11.234 --> 1:11:16.906
If you try and ignore it,
it'll just squeeze you
even harder.

1:11:18.007 --> 1:11:20.544
You'll think
about your future,

1:11:20.644 --> 1:11:23.513
but all you'll see
is your past.

1:11:23.613 --> 1:11:28.618
You'll hear them screaming,
glass breaking,

1:11:28.718 --> 1:11:31.855
everything falling apart
around you.

1:11:31.955 --> 1:11:35.992
And you'll remember
that's where it all leads.

1:11:37.193 --> 1:11:39.863
Mom never leaving
the house again.

1:11:39.963 --> 1:11:42.065
Dad drinking himself to death.

1:11:42.699 --> 1:11:44.233
Which one are you gonna be?

1:11:44.368 --> 1:11:45.769
Huh? Huh?

1:11:45.869 --> 1:11:47.537
Stop.

1:11:47.637 --> 1:11:49.506
Can't breathe, can you?

1:11:49.606 --> 1:11:52.576
Feel like you're gonna die?
Please stop. Stop!

1:11:52.676 --> 1:11:54.243
Why?

1:11:54.378 --> 1:11:57.180
I thought you loved
being human.

1:11:57.280 --> 1:11:59.716
You wanna feel everything
that we feel.

1:12:00.984 --> 1:12:03.653
Don't you? Don't you?

1:12:22.706 --> 1:12:26.776
There's none left.
Nothing's gonna save you.

1:12:30.046 --> 1:12:32.416
You will always be broken.

1:12:33.483 --> 1:12:34.718
You're worthless.

1:12:35.919 --> 1:12:37.587
You'll never be happy.

1:12:38.422 --> 1:12:40.089
What's the fucking point
of you?

1:12:40.189 --> 1:12:43.092
Stop, please. Please.
I can't breathe.

